# Cardano Contribution Ladder Framework

---

# Overview

## Summary
The Cardano Contribution Ladder Framework is a structured progression system developed through the Open Source Committee (OSC) under Intersect to guide contributors from newcomers into long-term ecosystem maintainers and leaders. The framework establishes transparent pathways for contributor growth, mentorship, recognition, governance participation, and operational stewardship across the Cardano ecosystem. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

The framework is designed to reduce contributor friction, improve ecosystem sustainability, and formalize pathways into trusted roles within decentralized open source environments.

---

## Objective
The framework aims to:
- Create transparent contributor pathways
- Reduce onboarding barriers
- Encourage long-term contributor retention
- Support maintainer succession planning
- Foster decentralized ecosystem stewardship
- Improve contribution quality
- Strengthen ecosystem sustainability
- Align contributor growth with ecosystem needs

---

## Why This Matters
Open source ecosystems often rely on informal social structures and undocumented expectations, creating:
- Maintainer burnout
- Contributor confusion
- Knowledge silos
- Governance centralization
- Weak succession planning
- High contributor drop-off rates

The Cardano Contribution Ladder attempts to operationalize contributor development through structured progression stages, mentorship, recognition systems, and governance-aligned participation. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

