## Why This Best Practice Fits the Lab
The Contribution Ladder Framework represents a practical governance and operational pattern for decentralized ecosystems attempting to solve long-term sustainability and contributor coordination challenges.

It demonstrates how ecosystems can:
- Develop contributor succession pathways
- Operationalize ecosystem stewardship
- Reduce dependency on centralized maintainers
- Improve contributor retention
- Build governance legitimacy through participation pathways
- Scale open source coordination sustainably

As decentralized ecosystems mature, structured human coordination systems like contribution ladders may become foundational infrastructure alongside technical protocols themselves.

